 should be paying for space outside of school property. The fact that the parents and the Iman does not insist that their child worshippers return to school after lunch is an issue their parents and their church are responsible for solving. The school is not. &#10;The more you separate groups of people by ethnicity, religion, lifestyle etc the more you emphasize the differences between people. Its much easier to breed prejudices in isolated groups. If we are going to have a multicultural society that works we need to bring children together to see how similar they are.not teach them that others are different. &#10;Religion belongs at home - not in the public school system."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="976" language="en" documentId="1530" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Kathena" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1530" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="235"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="236" end="563"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="564" end="916"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="917" end="976"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>